B.a_p={grammar:0,vocabulary:1,reading:2,translation:3,fill_blanks:4,sentence_completion:5}
B.mN={pilot:0,atc:1,cabin_crew:2,student:3}
B.a3D=new A.R("Modal Verbs & Conditional Structures","Gaps in grammar directly affect clearance readbacks and PIREP accuracy. Focus on shall/must/should and if-clauses in operational contexts.")
B.a3S=new A.R("Tense Consistency in Instructions","Inconsistent tense usage causes ambiguity in traffic information. Practice passive voice and future tense in ATC coordination phrases.")
B.a4f=new A.R("Imperative & Modal Structures","Safety announcements require precise imperative and modal grammar. Passengers must receive unambiguous instructions in emergency situations.")
B.a4P=new A.R("Core Aviation Grammar Patterns","Master modal verbs, passive constructions, and conditional sentences \u2014 the three pillars of ICAO standard aviation English grammar.")
B.Zw=new A.bs(B.mN,[B.a3D,B.a3S,B.a4f,B.a4P],t.dM)
B.a4I=new A.R("METAR/TAF & NOTAMs Terminology","Weather and NOTAM vocabulary is critical for pre-flight planning and in-flight decision making. Build your decoding speed for METAR abbreviations.")
B.a4U=new A.R("SID/STAR & Holding Phraseology","Precise vocabulary for departure and arrival procedures prevents misunderstandings in high-traffic environments. Focus on ICAO Doc 4444 phraseology.")
B.a4L=new A.R("Safety Equipment Terminology","Accurate names for safety equipment and procedures are non-negotiable for ICAO compliance and passenger safety management.")
B.a3N=new A.R("ICAO Core Aviation Vocabulary","Build your foundation with ATC phraseology, aircraft systems vocabulary, and standard ICAO terminology used across all aviation roles.")
B.Zx=new A.bs(B.mN,[B.a4I,B.a4U,B.a4L,B.a3N],t.dM)
B.a47=new A.R("Operational Document Comprehension","Slow reading of NOTAMs and OFPs under time pressure is a common exam failure point. Practice extracting key data from dense aviation texts in under 90 seconds.")
B.a46=new A.R("Flight Plan & Strip Reading Speed","ATC strips and flight plan formats contain dense information that must be processed rapidly. Drill reading speed on ICAO flight plan formats.")
B.a5r=new A.R("Safety Procedure Manuals","Understanding company ops manuals and ICAO safety documents in English is required for all cabin crew roles. Focus on procedural language patterns.")
B.a3E=new A.R("Aviation Text Comprehension","ICAO English exams include dense operational texts. Practice reading NOTAMs, METARs, and AIP extracts \u2014 focus on identifying key information quickly.")
B.Zv=new A.bs(B.mN,[B.a47,B.a46,B.a5r,B.a3E],t.dM)
B.mO={pilot:0,atc:1,student:2,cabin_crew:3}
B.a4_=new A.R("Operational Meaning Interpretation","Accurately interpreting the intent of ATC instructions and translating concepts between English and your working language prevents dangerous misunderstandings.")
B.a3K=new A.R("Readback & Clearance Precision","Translation errors in clearance readbacks are a leading cause of runway incursions. Practice precision in both directions without paraphrasing critical values.")
B.a5_=new A.R("Context-Based Language Transfer","Focus on understanding aviation texts in context rather than word-for-word translation. ICAO language is formulaic \u2014 learn the patterns.")
B.a3Y=new A.R("Safety Communication Accuracy","Translating safety instructions accurately ensures passenger compliance. Focus on official ICAO safety terminology rather than free translation.")
B.ZR=new A.bs(B.mO,[B.a4_,B.a3K,B.a5_,B.a3Y],t.dM)
B.a3B=new A.R("Aviation Collocations & Fixed Phrases",'Many ATC communications use fixed collocations (e.g. "cleared for", "report passing"). Recognition of these patterns is tested directly in fill-in-the-blank questions.')
B.a3I=new A.R("Standard Phraseology Patterns","Fill-in-the-blank questions test your knowledge of ICAO Doc 4444 standard phrases. Memorize the exact wording of common clearances and instructions.")
B.a58=new A.R("Aviation Collocation Patterns","Aviation English uses specific word combinations that don't follow general English rules. Study collocations from ICAO training materials systematically.")
B.a4s=new A.R("Safety Announcement Templates","Standard safety announcements follow fixed templates. Master the exact phrasing for each type of announcement \u2014 these appear frequently in fill-blank exams.")
B.ZP=new A.bs(B.mO,[B.a3B,B.a3I,B.a58,B.a4s],t.dM)
B.a3J=new A.R("Discourse Flow in ATC Communication","Understanding how ATC/pilot exchanges are structured helps predict how sentences complete. Study the logical flow of standard communication sequences.")
B.a4G=new A.R("Logical Sequence in Clearances","Clearance sentences follow predictable logical patterns. Practice completing partial clearances to build speed and accuracy on this question type.")
B.a3X=new A.R("Aviation Sentence Structure","Aviation English sentences follow specific structural patterns. Study how information is sequenced in ICAO communications \u2014 what comes first, second, third.")
B.a4X=new A.R("Procedural Language Completion","Safety and service procedure sentences follow predictable structures. Practice with official cabin crew communication scripts to internalize the patterns.")
B.ZQ=new A.bs(B.mO,[B.a3J,B.a4G,B.a3X,B.a4X],t.dM)
